Reasoning: 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper discusses guidelines for improving spreadsheet quality and user attitudes towards spreadsheet maintenance. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper mentions keeping business logic out of code, which relates to programming language design. 
- cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper discusses making spreadsheets safe to use and reducing risk. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also a possible category as the paper discusses changing user attitudes towards spreadsheet maintenance.
